getSum(uint256,uint256).details: getSum function is used to demonstrate the example library that I included to meet the projectrequirements. I suppose it's worth mentioning that the input isn't controlled so there is theopportunity for the user to overflow the result. This function is part of the Truffle tests.
getSum(uint256,uint256).return: a uint that is the sum of num1 and num2

removeAdmin(address).details: removeAdmin function is used to remove an address from the adminArray and set adminMapping bool to false.

removeOwner(address).details: removeOwner function is used to remove an address from the ownerArray and set ownerMapping bool to false.

params._currentOwnerAddress: is the address of the owner to remove

removeStore(uint256).details: removeStore function is used to remove a store from the store array in the ownersToStores mapping.There should be a storeRemoved event, but I didn't have time. The transaction sender (owner) can onlyaccess their own store array. In fact, the admins can't remove stores. Now that I thinkabout it, although the admins can remove owners, the stores of the removed owners will still exist inthe ownersToStores mapping. I don't have time to address this.

params._removeStoreIndex: is index of the store in the store array in the ownersToStores mapping.
